The City of Cape Town says lost trading hours means businesses are struggling to keep afloat. Lindsay Dentlinger has more details. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Curfew hours must change to save businesses. That’s the word from the City of Cape Town to government. READ: SA Lockdown: South Africa remains on alert level 3 The city says lost trading hours means businesses are struggling to keep afloat. It has written to Cooperative Governance Minister to reconsider curfew hours. The City says it’s yet to quantify the impact of lockdown on business closures, but for those still trading, an extended curfew could be the difference between make or break.